media:group.media:description:
Commission on Human Rights is now reviewing the human rights abuses committed during the enhanced community quarantine, spokesperson Jacqueline Ann de Guia said. "When you enforce punishments, which is a consequence of a wrong committed, which we are not against, ang sabi lang natin sana in accordance with the law, hindi sumobra, hindi sariling punishment nila, hindi sariling imbento nila," she said.
